{# 
    Canvas (<canvas>)
    ===========================================================================
    Used to draw graphics on the fly via scripting (usually JavaScript).

    Variables:
    - `canvas_id`: The id attribute of the canvas element. Defaults to "myCanvas".
    - `canvas_width`: The width of the canvas. Defaults to "300".
    - `canvas_height`: The height of the canvas. Defaults to "150".

    Notes:
    - The `| e` filter is used to escape any special characters in the variables
      to prevent XSS attacks.

    Links:
    - https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/canvas
    - https://www.w3schools.com/tags/tag_canvas.asp

#}

<canvas 
    id="{{ canvas_id | default('myCanvas') | e }}" 
    width="{{ canvas_width | default('300') | e }}" 
    height="{{ canvas_height | default('150') | e }}"
>
    Your browser does not support the canvas element.
</canvas>
